The paper proposes a method for large displacement optical flow using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and conditional random fields (CRFs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses learning binary descriptors, which is a topic commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of binary descriptors for efficient matching also suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses memory complexity reduction, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO).
